==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epigraph
<hw>Ep"i*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/:
cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧pigraphe</ets>. See <er>Epigram</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Any inscription set upon a building; especially, one
which has to do with the building itself, its founding or
dedication.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Literature)</fld> <def>A citation from some author,
or a sentence framed for the purpose, placed at the beginning of a work
or of its separate divisions; a motto.</def></p>

<p><ent>Epigraphical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Epigraphic</ent>⟦br⟧
